settings.description: Mario finds a rest area and stays there to pass some time before he's ready to fight bowser. It seems inside it is testing gizmos. Cloud Land 3 is next.
Mario Adventures Through the clouds to get to Bowsers Castle, nowhere near yet...
A unique idea of a triangular level.
Suppose it's time for an old washed up mario flash level maker to step foot into a new light... with a new honestly great level making program as well! hopefully this level's fun too!
Demake of the first level of the fangame smbddx
This is a replica of the very first Level of "Plok!" for the SNES. Also, its a test to see how well this editor was and to be honest, is kinda frustrating, but thats expected for a project in Alpha.
Warning : This level might be buggy
Wendy gets her Airship redesigned, With various Airships added for assistant, Mario goes to the airship by using an mini airship instead of climbing, Good Luck Defeating Wendy & Finding a Secret Exit
Embarking a Journey on the First Unused level but It's Improved by a little bit, Good luck finding the hidden Ace coins!

A remake of an unused level hidden in SMB3 NES/All-Stars SNES ROM.
I wanted to use Wrap Around but I gave up because many objects didn't go in intended positions.
Collect the coins while Flying, Don't forget the challenge perk!

Remake of the first Switch Palace in Super Mario World.
The Bonus Room Checkered Floors/Ceilings are glitched when they are longer than 15 tiles so I had to separate them with Unbreakable SMB1 Blocks.
A remake of Super Mario World 1-2. No Yoshi here, so Goomba Shoe is used instead.
REISSUE: Galoombas walk around in their peaceful hills, with lots of sandy and thin structures. I'm absolutely running out of levels. Prod. Code: 107, Rel: 6/2/22 -- 10:55 am
